# Number Systems in Digital Electronics

A number system is a method used to represent numbers using a set of digits or symbols. 
Digital systems use different number systems to represent and process data.

## Types of Number Systems

1. Decimal Number System (Base 10)
Digits used: 0–9  
Example: 245

2. Binary Number System (Base 2)
Digits used: 0 and 1  
Used in computers and digital circuits.

Example: 1011

3. Octal Number System (Base 8)
Digits used: 0–7  
Example: 17

4. Hexadecimal Number System (Base 16)
Digits used: 0–9 and A–F  
Example: 2A

## Importance in Digital Electronics
Binary number system is mainly used in digital electronics because digital circuits operate using two states: 0 and 1.
